      • printOneDBarcode

        public final void printOneDBarcode(int x,
                                   int y,
                                   PPLZOrient orient,
                                   int narrow,
                                   int wide,
                                   int height,
                                   PPLZBarCodeType type,
                                   int increase,
                                   byte[] data,
                                   char p1,
                                   char p2,
                                   char p3,
                                   char p4,
                                   char p5)
                            throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                                   BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to draw a one-dimensional barcode.
        Parameters:
        x - [in] X-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        y - [in] Y-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        orient - [in] Print orientation. Use PPLZOrient enum to set up.
        narrow - [in] Narrow bar width (also known as module width), the purpose is to magnify. Range: 1~10; unit: pixels.
        wide - [in] Wide bar width. Range: wide/narrow = 2.0~3.0; please refer to "Wide bar to narrow bar width ratio" of "One-dimensional barcode types".
        height - [in] Barcode height. When 'type' = 'U','5', range: 1~9999; else, range: 1~32000; unit: pixels.
        type - [in] One-dimensional barcode types. Please refer to "type" in "One-dimensional barcode types"; Use PPLZBarCodeType enum to set up.
        increase - [in] Increment or decrement. If there is a "Serial Number" to be printed, the barcode information will be changed according to the value change of Serial Number, with 0~9 loop for numbers, and A~Z or a~z loop for alphabets.
        data - [in] Barcode information. Data type: byte array.
        p1 - [in] Barcode printing condition. Please refer to "parameter" in "One-dimensional barcode types".
        p2 - [in] Barcode printing condition. Please refer to "parameter" in "One-dimensional barcode types".
        p3 - [in] Barcode printing condition. Please refer to "parameter" in "One-dimensional barcode types".
        p4 - [in] Barcode printing condition. Please refer to "parameter" in "One-dimensional barcode types".
        p5 - [in] Barcode printing condition. Please refer to "parameter" in "One-dimensional barcode types".

        One-dimensional barcode types

      • printMaxiCode

        public final void printMaxiCode(int x,
                                int y,
                                PPLZMaxiCodeMode mode,
                                int service,
                                int country,
                                java.lang.String zipcode,
                                byte[] data,
                                int increase)
                         throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                                BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to draw MaxiCode barcode.
        Parameters:
        x - [in] X-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        y - [in] Y-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        mode - [in] MaxiCode mode. Use PPLZMaxiCodeMode enum to set up.
        • Mode_2 = Structured carrier message: Numeric postal code (U.S.).
        • Mode_3 = Structured carrier message: Alphanumeric postal code (non-U.S.).
        service - [in] Three digit class of service. Only valid in mode 2 and mode 3.
        country - [in] Three digit country code. Only valid in mode 2 and mode 3.
        zipcode - [in] Zip code. Only valid in mode 2 and mode 3.
        • mode 2: please input a nine-digit zip code (five-digit zip code + four-digit zip code extension), if no zip code extension, please input "0000".
        • mode 3: please enter a six-digit zip code.
        data - [in] Barcode information. Data type: byte array.
        increase - [in] Increment or decrement. If there is a "Serial Number" to be printed, the barcode information will be changed according to the value change of Serial Number, with 0~9 loop for numbers, and A~Z or a~z loop for alphabets.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.
        See Also:
        PPLZMaxiCodeMode

                       throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                              BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to draw PDF417 barcode.
        Parameters:
        x - [in] X-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        y - [in] Y-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        orient - [in] Print orientation. Use PPLZOrient enum to set up.
        height - [in] The height of each row. Range: 1~9999; unit: pixels.
        security - [in] Error correction level. Range: 0~8; 0 means error detection only, no correction.
        columns - [in] Number of columns of data to be used for coding. Range: 1~30; 0: means automatic.
        rows - [in] Number of rows of data to be used for coding. Range: 3~90; 0: means automatic.
        isTruncate - [in] Truncate right column indicator and stop pattern. 'true' is to truncate; 'false' is not to truncate.
        narrow - [in] Narrow bar width (also known as module width), the purpose is to magnify. Range: 1~10; unit: pixels.
        data - [in] Barcode information. Data type: byte array.
        increase - [in] Increment or decrement. If there is a "Serial Number" to be printed, the barcode information will be changed according to the value change of Serial Number, with 0~9 loop for numbers, and A~Z or a~z loop for alphabets.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.
        See Also:
        PPLZOrient

      • printAztecCode

        public final void printAztecCode(int x,
                                 int y,
                                 PPLZOrient orient,
                                 int magnification,
                                 int errCorrect,
                                 byte[] data,
                                 int increase)
                          throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                                 BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to draw Aztec barcode.
        Parameters:
        x - [in] X-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        y - [in] Y-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        orient - [in] Print orientation. Use PPLZOrient enum to set up.
        magnification - [in] Magnification. Range: 1~10.
        errCorrect - [in] Error correction level.
        • 0 = Default error correction level.
        • 01~99 = Error correction percentage (minimum).
        • 101~104 = 1 to 4-layer compact symbol.
        • 201~232 = 1 to 32-layer full-range symbol.
        • 300 = A simple Aztec "Rune".
        data - [in] Barcode information. Data type: byte array.
        increase - [in] Increment or decrement. If there is a "Serial Number" to be printed, the barcode information will be changed according to the value change of Serial Number, with 0~9 loop for numbers, and A~Z or a~z loop for alphabets.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.

      • printRSS

        public final void printRSS(int x,
                           int y,
                           PPLZOrient orient,
                           PPLZRSSType type,
                           int magnification,
                           int height,
                           int segment,
                           byte[] data)
                    throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                           BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to draw RSS (Reduced Space Symbology) barcode. This barcode is also known as GS1 DataBar.
        Parameters:
        x - [in] X-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        y - [in] Y-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        orient - [in] Print orientation. Use PPLZOrient enum to set up.
        type - [in] Symbology type. Use PPLZRSSType enum to set up.
        magnification - [in] Magnification. Range: 1~10.
        height - [in] Barcode height. Range: 1~32000; unit: pixels; 0 is the barcode standard value; please refer to "Standard minimum height of symbology type" of "Symbology types of RSS (GS1 DataBar)".
        segment -

        [in] Maximum number of data blocks can be contained in each row of bar code. The parameter is valid only when RSS Expanded bar code; invalid for other types of RSS barcode.

        Range: 2~22 (the value has to be even); default value: 22.

        When the value is 22, it is RSS Expanded; then the value is not 22, it is RSS Expanded Stacked.

        data -

        [in] Barcode information. Data type: byte array.

        Data format of one-dimensional barcode is [1D Data]. For example: "00614141999996".

        Data format of one/two-dimensional barcode is [1D Data]|[2D Composite Data], use character '|' to separate 1D/2D data. For example: "00614141999996|RSS test".

        Symbology types of RSS (GS1 DataBar)

        type Description of symbology type

        Standard minimum height of symbology type

        (Unit: Pixels)
        1 RSS-14 (GS1 DataBar Omnidirectional). 33
        2 RSS Truncated (GS1 DataBar Truncated). 13
        3 RSS Stacked (GS1 DataBar Stacked). 13
        4 RSS Stacked Omnidirectional (GS1 DataBar Stacked Omnidirectional). 69
        5 RSS Limited (GS1 DataBar Limited). 10
        6 RSS Expanded (GS1 DataBar Expanded). 34
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.
        See Also:
        PPLZOrient, PPLZRSSType

                                  int y,
                                  PPLZOrient orient,

        This function is used to draw Data Matrix barcode, and quality level only supports ECC 200.
        Parameters:
        x - [in] X-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.
        y - [in] Y-axis coordinate. Range: 0~32000; unit: pixels.

        height - [in] Dimensional height of individual symbol elements. Range: 1~9999; unit: pixels.
        columns - [in] Number of columns of data to be used for coding. Range: 9~49; 0: means automatic; when in ECC 200, this value only support even value.
        rows - [in] Number of rows of data to be used for coding. Range: 9~49; 0: means automatic; when in ECC 200, this value only support even value.
        data - [in] Barcode information. Data type: byte array.
        increase - [in] Increment or decrement. If there is a "Serial Number" to be printed, the barcode information will be changed according to the value change of Serial Number, with 0~9 loop for numbers, and A~Z or a~z loop for alphabets.
